{
          pages:[
              "[
                \"\",
                {\"text\":\"§osmudged writing, wear and tear lines the edges of the paper
\"},
                {\"text\":\" ... considering how that last human fellow turned out, I could be worse for wear. Then again, my expeditions could bear a bit more fruit with less risk.\"}
              ]",
              "[
                {\"text\":\"Could also do with one less raid, but then we might as well be asking for daily miracles. Anyway, I'm taking up too much ink letting my own thoughts babble, and my crew wants me to keep up...\"}
              ]",
              "[
                {\"text\":\"§lEntry #3: Carvings from the Inside Out
\"},
                {\"text\":\"The beams along the walls seem to be made from a form of stone masonry. The material suggests dripstone, an underground stalactite.\"}
              ]",
              "[
                {\"text\":\"A rather unusual type of rock, but the work done for these etchings is rather impeccable.\"}
              ]",
              "[
                {\"text\":\"Sturdy too! This could be considered less of a hypothesis and more of a guess, because the evidence isn't fully put together, but I have a feeling the builders of this mineshaft actually come from below ground!\"}
              ]",
              "[
                {\"text\":\"If not below, then at the very least familiar and prefer their home beneath the strata. \"}
              ]",
              "[
                {\"text\":\"Considering these caves rely more on natural lighting from the local flora, then these must be seasoned cavers that had spent a very long time down here.\"}
              ]",
              "[
                {\"text\":\"Where the shafts are being dug from, my best guess is to follow where the beams were installed and see where they lead...\"}
              ]",
              "[
                {\"text\":\"If we can get past the cold chills and groaning, that is.\"}
              ]"
            ],
            title:Journal,
            author:Unkown,
            display:{Lore:["Found in the Ancient Mines"]}
            }

{
          pages:[
              "[
                \"\",
                {\"text\":\"§lEntry #4: A Very Deep Pit
\"},
                {\"text\":\"The entry title is rather self-explanatory, but I think it also gives more credence to the underground dwellers theory.\"}
              ]",
              "[
                {\"text\":\"We just found a second pit similar to the one seen near the entrance, but this one doesn't smell like bubbling rotten eggs caressing bits of cobble.\"}
              ]",
              "[
                {\"text\":\"It's really dark down this pit, and a self-funded expedition with backup doesn't give any room for medical care or injuries. \"}
              ]",
              "[
                {\"text\":\"When did that ever stop me, though? I want to see what else lies below, especially if it gives credence to some of the stories my parents told me about! If they are what I think they are, then I can't wait to see what lies below!\"}
              ]",
              "[
                {\"text\":\"Just need to be brave, and ignore the pit forming in my stomach...\"}
              ]"
            ],
            title:Journal,
            author:Unkown,
            display:{Lore:["Found in the Ancient Mines"]}
            }

